    pearls: ["SMART works because formoterol has RAPID onset (1-3 min) like albuterol — salmeterol (Advair) has slow onset (15-30 min) and CANNOT be used for SMART","Using ICS-formoterol as rescue automatically increases anti-inflammatory dose during worsening — SABA rescue only bronchodilates without treating the underlying inflammation","GINA 2023: as-needed ICS-formoterol is now PREFERRED over SABA alone even for MILD (Step 1-2) asthma","≥3 SABA canisters per year is associated with increased exacerbation risk and mortality — this is the key metric driving the paradigm shift away from SABA-only rescue","SMART reduces severe exacerbations by 30-50% compared to fixed-dose ICS-LABA + SABA rescue","Maximum total daily dose for SMART: typically up to 12 inhalations (maintenance + rescue combined)","Patients must understand they are using ONE inhaler for TWO purposes — proper education is essential for SMART success"],
